WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:03.620 --> 00:05.420
Previously on
Andi Mack...

00:05.420 --> 00:07.040
You need to go talk
to Coleman.

00:07.040 --> 00:10.330
-About what?
-Kinda told him that you
did my homework.

00:10.330 --> 00:11.830
Buffy:
I'm suspended
from the team.

00:11.830 --> 00:13.460
That's so unfair!

00:13.460 --> 00:15.920
I'm starting a girl's
basketball team.

00:15.920 --> 00:17.290
Bowie, you should
be a guitar teacher.

00:17.290 --> 00:19.500
He's amazing.
By my second lesson,

00:19.500 --> 00:22.790
he had me writing a song,
and my third was performing
on the stage.

00:22.790 --> 00:26.290
♪ Words to make you stay... ♪

00:26.290 --> 00:28.460
I think this song
is about you.

00:28.460 --> 00:31.460
♪ The only thing I wish for ♪

00:31.460 --> 00:35.290
♪ Is being around you ♪

00:35.290 --> 00:38.580
-I just want to be friends.
-I want to be friends, too.

00:38.580 --> 00:42.250
So, we both want to go back
to just being friends...

00:42.250 --> 00:44.790
But you don't want to break up
with me, and I don't want
to break up with you.

00:44.790 --> 00:48.460
-Is that allowed?
-I think we just did it.

00:48.460 --> 00:50.500
Andi:
I do feel weird
around Walker.

00:50.500 --> 00:54.420
You don't really want him
to come to the Color Factory
with us, do you?

00:54.420 --> 00:56.420
I'm sorry.

00:56.420 --> 00:59.000
Andi:
They are having
a blast without me.

00:59.000 --> 01:02.000
-Why aren't you there?
-I can't. I mean, with Buffy,

01:02.000 --> 01:03.620
when she's with Walker...

01:03.620 --> 01:06.580
and she'd rather be
with Walker
than with me...

01:10.040 --> 01:11.380
♪ ♪

01:11.380 --> 01:14.380
Mmm, this is so good.

01:14.380 --> 01:16.460
Just so you know,
when we're living together,

01:16.460 --> 01:17.710
you're making these
every day.

01:17.710 --> 01:20.210
That reminds me!
I can't believe I forgot
to tell you!

01:20.210 --> 01:21.620
Our lease...

01:21.620 --> 01:23.540
-it was accepted.
-What?!

01:23.540 --> 01:24.920
-When?!
-This morning!

01:24.920 --> 01:25.920
We got the new place.

01:25.920 --> 01:26.960
We got the new place!

01:26.960 --> 01:29.420
Wait, wait, excuse me.
Are you two moving?

01:29.420 --> 01:31.290
We're gonna need
a bigger place when
we get married.

01:31.290 --> 01:33.540
And you didn't think to tell me?

01:33.540 --> 01:34.620
I mean, we had
a family meeting

01:34.620 --> 01:37.290
about changing
breakfast cereals!

01:37.290 --> 01:38.420
But this was a secret?

01:38.420 --> 01:40.920
-It has two bathrooms.
-Two bathrooms?

01:40.920 --> 01:43.580
And closets, and a place
for a washer and dryer...

01:43.580 --> 01:44.830
And I'd get a bedroom.

01:44.830 --> 01:46.540
I mean, I can't crash
on your couch forever, Andi.

01:46.540 --> 01:48.540
Let's go there now!
I want to see it!

01:48.540 --> 01:50.620
There's not much to see.
It needs work.

01:50.620 --> 01:52.210
Oh, but we do have pictures!

01:52.210 --> 01:53.460
Show me the pictures!

01:53.460 --> 01:55.500
I left them in my car.
I'll be right back.

01:55.500 --> 01:58.540
I can't believe you went
looking for our home
without me.

01:58.540 --> 02:01.210
We wanted to surprise you.

02:01.210 --> 02:02.500
Surprises!

02:02.500 --> 02:05.580
You treat me like a little kid.
I don't need surprises.

02:05.580 --> 02:06.500
(smash)

02:06.500 --> 02:07.380
(Andi screams)

02:07.380 --> 02:09.290
What is happening?!
Do something!

02:11.170 --> 02:13.500
-Surprise!
-It's the new place!

02:13.500 --> 02:14.750
The apartment next door!

02:14.750 --> 02:16.000
I'm gonna knock
this wall down,

02:16.000 --> 02:17.880
before you know it,
we'll have one big apartment!

02:20.170 --> 02:22.790
(chuckling)
Okay, fine.
That was a good surprise.

02:26.120 --> 02:29.620
♪ I'm standin'
on the edge ♪

02:29.620 --> 02:34.120
♪ And everything I know-oh-oh
is blown away ♪

02:35.670 --> 02:38.830
♪ Life is upside down ♪

02:38.830 --> 02:43.540
♪ But any way it goes
I'll work it out ♪

02:45.210 --> 02:48.620
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh ♪

02:48.620 --> 02:52.580
♪ Here we go ♪

02:52.580 --> 02:55.580
-♪ One, two, three ♪
-♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:55.580 --> 02:57.750
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

02:57.750 --> 03:00.250
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

03:00.250 --> 03:02.580
♪ But I'm with you all the way

03:02.580 --> 03:05.210
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

03:05.210 --> 03:07.540
-♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

03:07.540 --> 03:09.750
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

03:09.750 --> 03:12.580
-♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

03:12.580 --> 03:14.580
♪ All the way ♪

03:19.040 --> 03:22.460
♪ ♪

03:25.210 --> 03:27.170
Nervous?

03:27.170 --> 03:29.710
No. Why would I be nervous?

03:29.710 --> 03:32.250
Because you're about to start
a girls basketball team.

03:32.250 --> 03:34.880
Only the entire history
of this school and your future

03:34.880 --> 03:37.500
will depend on what's on
the other side of this door.

03:37.500 --> 03:39.380
Still not nervous.

03:39.380 --> 03:41.540
You think anyone showed up?

03:41.540 --> 03:44.330
-Yeah...
-What if you walk
through that door,

03:44.330 --> 03:46.880
and nobody's there?

03:46.880 --> 03:50.170
I feel like you guys
are deliberately trying
to make me nervous.

03:50.170 --> 03:51.500
It's not going to work.

03:51.500 --> 03:54.670
See? I told him.
You're a rock.

03:54.670 --> 03:57.250
And now he owes me
the muffin of my choice.

04:08.670 --> 04:11.960
Okay, now I'm nervous.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.750
Blueberry macadamia.

04:13.750 --> 04:15.580
There's no such muffin.

04:15.580 --> 04:17.880
Then, I guess you have
your work cut out for you.

04:22.330 --> 04:26.170
Hey, welcome. Glad you guys
showed up. I'm Buffy.

04:26.170 --> 04:29.670
(rap music starts)

04:29.670 --> 04:30.460
(blows whistle)

04:32.670 --> 04:34.170
♪ Don't be a fool
by the cool ♪

04:34.170 --> 04:35.960
♪ What we do yeah,
we put in the work ♪

04:35.960 --> 04:37.920
♪ I guess I'm young, wild,
and outta control ♪

04:37.920 --> 04:40.750
♪ They say I'm angry,
but understand yo ♪

04:40.750 --> 04:43.080
♪ We don't talk it like now,
we go toe-to-toe ♪

04:43.080 --> 04:45.460
♪ I gave my heart uh,
but now they want my soul ♪

04:45.460 --> 04:47.620
-(blows whistle)
-Okay, let's go!

04:47.620 --> 04:50.290
Buffy:
Shoot with one hand, not two!

04:50.290 --> 04:51.750
(blows whistle)

04:51.750 --> 04:54.080
♪ What kinda man stands
with his hand out? ♪

04:54.080 --> 04:55.420
♪ Get your hustle up ♪

04:55.420 --> 04:58.540
Buffy:
Touch the line! Ease up!
Don't drag your feet!

04:58.540 --> 05:02.000
♪ Chris Paul throw you along
And help my man out ♪

05:02.000 --> 05:03.120
♪ They see the life ♪

05:03.120 --> 05:04.710
♪ They see us winnin' ♪

05:04.710 --> 05:07.040
♪ And I guess they think
it's all free ♪

05:07.040 --> 05:08.580
♪ They see the claws ♪

05:08.580 --> 05:10.080
♪ They see the trees ♪

05:10.080 --> 05:11.710
♪ They wasn't there to see me
roll up my sleeves ♪

05:11.710 --> 05:13.620
♪ I put in work ♪

05:13.620 --> 05:16.170
♪ I know I make it
look easy ♪

05:16.170 --> 05:17.460
♪ But yo, you gotta
believe me ♪

05:17.460 --> 05:20.170
You know what?
Let's take a break.

05:23.920 --> 05:26.830
(sighs)
This is a nightmare.

05:26.830 --> 05:28.290
Nobody's going to
want to coach us.

05:28.290 --> 05:29.460
They're terrible.

05:29.460 --> 05:32.000
They're not terrible.
They're just not you.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.210
What does that mean?

05:34.210 --> 05:36.000
That it's tryouts.

05:36.000 --> 05:37.750
They're out
and they're trying.

05:37.750 --> 05:39.500
That's all you can expect.

05:39.500 --> 05:41.380
They need encouragement.

05:41.380 --> 05:42.710
Positive reinforcement.

05:42.710 --> 05:45.170
I'm supposed to take
your advice after how you

05:45.170 --> 05:47.210
treated me when I was
on your team?

05:47.210 --> 05:50.080
Well, you're lookin' like
the kinda captain I was.

05:50.080 --> 05:53.670
-Is that what you want to be?
-No.

05:53.670 --> 05:56.580
(rock music)

05:56.580 --> 05:57.710
Ooh! I got one!

05:57.710 --> 06:00.380
-Me, too!
-Me, first.

06:00.380 --> 06:02.380
(laughs)
Hilarious.

06:02.380 --> 06:03.750
-(camera clicks)
-(both giggle)

06:03.750 --> 06:05.080
Here, my turn.

06:06.330 --> 06:09.210
(laughs)
Perfect. Don't move.

06:09.210 --> 06:11.120
-(camera clicks)
-Got it.

06:11.120 --> 06:12.790
Can you even believe this?

06:12.790 --> 06:15.210
I know...
people still buy albums?

06:15.210 --> 06:18.670
No! I mean, our invention!
The "no break-up break-up."

06:18.670 --> 06:22.210
It works! I mean, look at us,
hanging out with no drama.

06:22.210 --> 06:23.580
I know! It's fun.

06:23.580 --> 06:25.710
Everything used to be
so complicated.

06:25.710 --> 06:27.330
You laughing when
I fell at the arcade.

06:27.330 --> 06:29.710
You buying me that piece of rice
with my name misspelled.

06:29.710 --> 06:32.000
(in unison)
The bracelet!

06:32.000 --> 06:35.040
Speaking of that...
I'm sure you've noticed...

06:35.040 --> 06:36.920
You're not wearing it anymore.

06:36.920 --> 06:37.880
I did notice.

06:37.880 --> 06:39.920
I may have lost it at camp.

06:39.920 --> 06:41.460
It's fine. I don't care.

06:41.460 --> 06:43.000
I thought you'd be mad.

06:43.000 --> 06:44.250
Honestly?

06:44.250 --> 06:45.580
I'm relieved.

06:45.580 --> 06:47.710
That thing was way more trouble
than it was worth.

06:48.920 --> 06:51.790
Hey, I'm putting together a list
for open mic tomorrow night.

06:51.790 --> 06:54.290
Got any preference on time slot?

06:54.290 --> 06:55.380
Why would I need a time slot?

06:55.380 --> 06:57.250
Because you're on
the list to play.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.880
And, right now, you...

06:59.880 --> 07:02.790
yep, you are the only one
on the list, so you kind of
have to do it.

07:02.790 --> 07:04.170
I only have one song.

07:04.170 --> 07:07.790
You're a one-hit-wonder!
People have built careers
on less.

07:07.790 --> 07:08.880
Do you want to open or close?

07:10.290 --> 07:11.170
You could do both.

07:11.170 --> 07:12.790
I can't play that song again.

07:12.790 --> 07:14.960
He absolutely can't.

07:14.960 --> 07:17.790
-Then, I guess you're gonna
have to write another one.
-I barely wrote the first one.

07:17.790 --> 07:19.170
But now you know how to do it!

07:19.170 --> 07:20.960
-I do?
-Bowie: Yeah!

07:20.960 --> 07:23.210
You just pick a moment
in your life where you
felt something.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.500
One of the three.

07:25.500 --> 07:27.170
Three? Really, Andi?

07:27.170 --> 07:29.670
Sorry. That was mean.

07:29.670 --> 07:31.460
I can only think of two.

07:31.460 --> 07:34.000
(both laugh)

07:34.000 --> 07:35.460
Ooh.

07:38.620 --> 07:39.710
♪ ♪

07:41.710 --> 07:43.120
(muffled disco playing)

07:48.330 --> 07:49.380
(yelling out)
Bowie!

07:49.380 --> 07:50.500
Bowie:
What?

07:50.500 --> 07:53.120
I'm trying to do yoga!

07:53.120 --> 07:54.830
Turn it up!

07:54.830 --> 07:58.250
-(disco music plays louder)
-Thank you!

07:58.250 --> 08:00.790
♪ Touchdown, street sounds ♪

08:00.790 --> 08:02.960
♪ Go crazy for the
New York ladies ♪

08:02.960 --> 08:04.880
♪ Kick back,
lookin' around ♪

08:04.880 --> 08:06.920
♪ Summer in the city,
goin' underground ♪

08:06.920 --> 08:09.040
♪ Break out, hit the town♪

08:09.040 --> 08:11.210
♪ Go crazy for the
drop top ladies ♪

08:11.210 --> 08:13.420
♪ Beats off, face out ♪

08:13.420 --> 08:15.670
♪ The rhythm of life,
drop it to the ground ♪

08:15.670 --> 08:18.460
(scoffs)
What are you doing?

08:18.460 --> 08:21.830
Disco-yoga!

08:21.830 --> 08:23.920
Okay, we have a problem.

08:23.920 --> 08:25.170
What is it?

08:25.170 --> 08:26.880
Away from the hole.

08:26.880 --> 08:30.830
♪ Take this party
higher on the floor ♪

08:30.830 --> 08:32.000
What's up?

08:32.000 --> 08:34.290
All my special shower stuff
is missing!

08:34.290 --> 08:35.580
What do you mean "missing"?

08:35.580 --> 08:37.790
I mean, it's not in the shower!

08:37.790 --> 08:41.080
My eucalyptus body scrub,
my charcoal soap...
they're all gone!

08:41.080 --> 08:42.620
Well, I didn't take them.

08:42.620 --> 08:44.960
I know... he did.

08:46.040 --> 08:48.080
Bowie?

08:48.080 --> 08:50.710
Yes! I mean, he had access,
he had opportunity, he's
the only one that would--

08:50.710 --> 08:53.080
-Easy!
-You think this is funny.

08:53.080 --> 08:56.710
I think this is a
new situation for all of us.

08:56.710 --> 08:58.040
We just have
to learn to adapt.

08:58.040 --> 08:59.920
Oh, really? Well...

08:59.920 --> 09:02.290
your special shower stuff
is missing too.

09:03.670 --> 09:04.920
What special shower stuff?

09:04.920 --> 09:06.920
Your coconut oil hair mask.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.790
Oh, that's fine.
I barely use it, anyway.

09:08.790 --> 09:11.920
-Your primrose conditioner.
-Plenty to go around.

09:11.920 --> 09:13.580
Your sea sponge.

09:16.880 --> 09:19.380
-(yells out)
Family meeting!
-Yep.

09:19.380 --> 09:21.420
(scoffs)

09:25.080 --> 09:27.040
You can't just go scouring
through our apartment

09:27.040 --> 09:28.500
like it's a
drug store aisle!

09:28.500 --> 09:30.040
What were you thinking?

09:30.040 --> 09:34.000
You forget. I was on
a tour bus for two months
with a bunch of dudes.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.960
You don't want to know
what we were using for soap.

09:36.960 --> 09:39.580
I mean, I was there,
and I don't even know.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.540
It's really hard
to be mad at you

09:41.540 --> 09:43.880
when your hair and skin
look this radiant.

09:43.880 --> 09:45.420
I feel like sunshine.

09:45.420 --> 09:48.500
Could you please
just ask next time,
before taking something?

09:48.500 --> 09:50.960
Absolutely.
It won't happen again.

09:52.830 --> 09:54.250
(sniffs)

09:56.420 --> 10:01.420
Did you use my over-priced
peppermint shampoo
as body wash?!

10:04.250 --> 10:05.920
Was that wrong?

10:05.920 --> 10:07.290
Yes, it was very wrong!

10:07.290 --> 10:08.960
-Why?!
-Because...

10:08.960 --> 10:12.750
one is shampoo,
and one is body wash.

10:12.750 --> 10:17.120
-They're all made
with the same stuff.
-(together) Just stop!

10:17.120 --> 10:19.000
♪ ♪

10:28.000 --> 10:29.040
Ooo...

10:29.040 --> 10:31.960
nobody signed up
for round two of tryouts?

10:31.960 --> 10:35.250
People tend to go on vacation
around the third week of school.

10:35.250 --> 10:37.500
Or maybe word got out
after the first round

10:37.500 --> 10:40.670
that the captain
was super cranky.

10:40.670 --> 10:43.540
It's easy for you.
You have more players
than you need.

10:43.540 --> 10:45.420
You have nine.
That should be enough.

10:45.420 --> 10:48.750
(scoffs)
They were flopping
all over the court.

10:48.750 --> 10:49.960
I mean, you were there!

10:49.960 --> 10:51.580
It was like teaching fish.

10:51.580 --> 10:53.460
Not so easy
leading a team, is it?

10:53.460 --> 10:55.670
No...

10:55.670 --> 10:58.290
and I feel like
nothing I say or do
will make a difference.

10:58.290 --> 11:02.170
Wow... there's that
can't-do spirit that makes
a great captain.

11:02.170 --> 11:05.920
What? They're never
going to look like a team.

11:09.080 --> 11:12.080
Unless...
they look like a team.

11:12.080 --> 11:14.290
You lost me.

11:14.290 --> 11:17.170
I think I need a favor.
You still owe me, right?

11:17.170 --> 11:18.830
♪ ♪

11:26.420 --> 11:29.210
-Oh, hey.
-Hey.

11:29.210 --> 11:31.210
How did Buffy's
basketball tryouts go?

11:31.210 --> 11:33.580
-Do you know?
-Yeah, I was there...

11:33.580 --> 11:36.290
-And...
-Why don't you
just ask Buffy?

11:38.290 --> 11:40.380
Have you not talked to her
since the Color Factory?

11:40.380 --> 11:42.040
No.

11:42.040 --> 11:45.080
And I was hoping
I could start a conversation
with, "Congratulations!"

11:45.080 --> 11:46.830
Yeah, you can't do that.

11:46.830 --> 11:49.040
(sighs)
Oh.

11:50.500 --> 11:52.960
Well, in that case,
I'm just gonna go
save some seats.

11:56.170 --> 11:58.920
I'm really proud of you, man.
You've come a long way.

11:58.920 --> 12:00.460
I mean, you wrote this song
all on your own.

12:00.460 --> 12:02.620
You might want
to hold that compliment
till you hear it.

12:02.620 --> 12:04.790
(chuckles)
Modest.

12:04.790 --> 12:08.620
-Good Hair Crew-- unite!
-(all chuckle)

12:10.080 --> 12:11.380
-Hey.
-Hi.

12:11.380 --> 12:13.120
I saved a seat for Walker,
in case he's coming.

12:13.120 --> 12:14.880
He's not.

12:14.880 --> 12:16.500
It looked like you had fun
at the Color Factory.

12:16.500 --> 12:17.620
Why didn't you come?

12:17.620 --> 12:19.790
Let's... not get into that.

12:21.080 --> 12:22.040
(sighs)

12:22.040 --> 12:23.710
How did basketball tryouts go?

12:23.710 --> 12:26.120
(scoffs)
Let's not get into that.

12:26.120 --> 12:29.790
Bowie: (over microphone)
All right, all right, you guys
ready for the show to start?

12:29.790 --> 12:32.250
-(clapping)
-Most definitely!

12:32.250 --> 12:36.330
Our first performer is making
his second appearance
here on stage.

12:36.330 --> 12:38.170
And we're lucky
to have him back.

12:38.170 --> 12:42.330
Give it up for Jonah Beck!

12:42.330 --> 12:44.170
(cheering, clapping)

12:47.670 --> 12:48.750
How's everyone doing tonight?

12:48.750 --> 12:50.170
Ooo. Patter.

12:50.170 --> 12:51.540
(calling out)
We're doing good!

12:51.540 --> 12:52.580
Glad to hear it!

12:52.580 --> 12:53.620
Nice shirt!

12:53.620 --> 12:56.000
-I'll take it from here.
-Okay.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.120
This is a new song.
Hope you like it.

13:00.210 --> 13:02.000
(guitar playing)

13:07.120 --> 13:09.710
♪ The night before I left ♪

13:09.710 --> 13:12.880
♪ I walked her to the door ♪

13:12.880 --> 13:16.210
♪ To say goodbye,
and she cried ♪

13:16.210 --> 13:18.540
♪ She cried ♪

13:18.540 --> 13:21.620
♪ She cry-ee-i-ee-ied ♪

13:21.620 --> 13:25.920
♪ She could not stop
the tears from falling ♪

13:25.920 --> 13:29.170
♪ No matter how hard
she tried ♪

13:29.170 --> 13:33.170
♪ And she cried,
she cried ♪

13:33.170 --> 13:34.040
What's wrong?

13:35.120 --> 13:36.710
This song's about me.

13:36.710 --> 13:39.580
♪ I never seen her
look so sad ♪

13:39.580 --> 13:42.500
♪ She must have been
in so much pain ♪

13:42.500 --> 13:44.880
This is not how it went down.

13:44.880 --> 13:48.460
I definitely did not cry,
and cry, and cry.

13:48.460 --> 13:50.750
♪ ...pouring rain ♪

13:50.750 --> 13:54.620
♪ I didn't know what to say ♪

13:54.620 --> 13:59.080
♪ Everything felt so wrong ♪

13:59.080 --> 14:02.210
♪ So I picked up my guitar ♪

14:02.210 --> 14:06.210
♪ And I wrote her
this song ♪

14:06.210 --> 14:08.830
♪ The night before I left ♪

14:08.830 --> 14:13.580
♪ I walked her to the door
to say goodbye ♪

14:13.580 --> 14:17.500
♪ And she cried, she cried ♪

14:17.500 --> 14:21.380
♪ She cry-ee-i-ee-ied ♪

14:21.380 --> 14:26.380
♪ She cry-ee-i-ee-i-
ee-i-ee-ied ♪

14:26.790 --> 14:30.040
-♪ Whoa-oh-oh ♪
-(cheering, applause)

14:34.380 --> 14:36.170
I'm fine.

14:39.170 --> 14:41.080
♪ ♪

14:45.250 --> 14:47.040
♪ ♪

14:53.460 --> 14:55.040
They're all staring at me.

14:57.210 --> 15:01.330
Yes! She's known
some heartbreak!

15:01.330 --> 15:04.000
Now, let's just let her
move past it! Yeah?

15:05.920 --> 15:09.880
There you are.
You took off last night
without saying goodbye.

15:09.880 --> 15:13.250
Well, at least I didn't cry,
and cry, and cry.

15:13.250 --> 15:15.620
And for the record,
I was a little misty,

15:15.620 --> 15:17.120
I wasn't watering the lawn!

15:17.120 --> 15:19.330
You didn't like it?

15:19.330 --> 15:21.580
Jonah, I was humiliated.

15:21.580 --> 15:24.250
You guys said to write
about a moment in my life
when I felt something.

15:24.250 --> 15:28.290
Right, when you felt something.

15:28.290 --> 15:29.880
Not when I felt something!

15:29.880 --> 15:31.380
But I did feel something.

15:31.380 --> 15:34.750
Well, you conveniently
left that part out.

15:34.750 --> 15:36.710
So, what can I do
to make it up to you?

15:38.080 --> 15:40.330
Can you un-sing what you sang?

15:46.420 --> 15:50.000
-Help!
-Easy, JB.
We can fix this.

15:50.000 --> 15:51.500
How?

15:51.500 --> 15:54.080
I have some ideas.
What kind of budget
are we working with?

15:54.080 --> 15:55.420
♪ ♪

15:58.670 --> 16:00.880
Well, you did it.

16:00.880 --> 16:03.040
I did, didn't I?

16:03.040 --> 16:06.960
(2 Unlimited -
"Get Ready for This" remix)

16:06.960 --> 16:10.920
-They look like a team.
-Now, I just have to get them
to play like a team.

16:10.920 --> 16:13.460
Hey, thanks for sharing
your jersey connection.

16:13.460 --> 16:16.170
If you need sneakers,
I also got a guy.

16:17.620 --> 16:19.330
Where are they going?

16:19.330 --> 16:22.670
I don't know.
They've been walking
around like that all day.

16:22.670 --> 16:24.290
They must really
like those uniforms.

16:26.170 --> 16:29.920
Can we please talk
about anything other
than Jonah's song?

16:29.920 --> 16:32.210
Sure. But I can't stop
thinking about it.

16:32.210 --> 16:33.460
Buffy:
Sorry, it's catchy!

16:33.460 --> 16:37.920
Especially the part
where he says:
(sings) " Cry-ee-i-ee-ied."

16:38.830 --> 16:43.380
And we don't change the subject,
then I-ee-I-ee-I'm leaving.

16:52.170 --> 16:53.040
(gasps)

16:54.540 --> 16:55.670
Please no.

16:58.290 --> 16:59.460
What is happening right now?

16:59.460 --> 17:02.920
I may not be able
to un-sing what I sang.

17:02.920 --> 17:04.080
But I can re-sing it.

17:05.330 --> 17:07.330
I really wish you wouldn't.

17:10.830 --> 17:13.330
(guitar playing)

17:18.540 --> 17:21.000
♪ The night before I left ♪

17:21.000 --> 17:25.420
♪ I walked her to the door
to say goodbye ♪

17:25.420 --> 17:27.830
-Here it comes.
-♪ And I cried ♪

17:27.830 --> 17:30.250
♪ I cried ♪

17:30.250 --> 17:33.250
♪ So many tears I cried ♪

17:33.250 --> 17:37.210
♪ I never ever felt so sad ♪

17:37.210 --> 17:40.460
♪ I've never been
in so much pain ♪

17:40.460 --> 17:45.250
♪ I never ever felt so bad ♪

17:45.250 --> 17:47.880
♪ Eyes look like
they're pourin' rain ♪

17:49.460 --> 17:53.460
♪ I didn't know what to say ♪

17:53.460 --> 17:57.620
♪ Everything felt so wrong ♪

17:59.040 --> 18:02.330
♪ So I picked up my guitar ♪

18:02.330 --> 18:06.170
♪ And I wrote her this song ♪

18:06.170 --> 18:08.710
♪ The night before I left ♪

18:08.710 --> 18:12.000
♪ I walked her to the door ♪

18:12.000 --> 18:15.790
♪ To say goodbye,
and I cried ♪

18:15.790 --> 18:17.420
♪ I cried ♪

18:17.420 --> 18:21.420
♪ I cry-ee-i-ee-ied ♪

18:22.580 --> 18:26.210
♪ I cried, I cried ♪

18:26.210 --> 18:31.000
♪ So many tears I cried ♪

18:34.620 --> 18:37.540
And that's how it went down.

18:37.540 --> 18:40.420
(applause)

18:40.420 --> 18:43.210
♪ ♪

18:47.790 --> 18:50.500
Remember how we were
congratulating ourselves

18:50.500 --> 18:53.750
for being able to hang out
with no drama or complications?

18:53.750 --> 18:55.380
We were so wrong.

18:55.380 --> 18:57.750
It's like a whole new set
of buttons have been installed,

18:57.750 --> 18:59.170
just waiting to be pushed.

18:59.170 --> 19:01.170
We're still pretty lucky
to have each other as exes.

19:01.170 --> 19:03.920
Are you kidding?
We are the Best Exes Ever.

19:03.920 --> 19:07.210
Best Exes Ever Forever.

19:07.210 --> 19:08.540
B.E.E.F's!

19:08.540 --> 19:10.500
Sure! Why not?

19:10.500 --> 19:12.920
And we'll always be able
to hang out at Red Rooster,

19:12.920 --> 19:14.290
no matter what
buttons get pushed.

19:14.290 --> 19:16.620
Even if it's the biggest button
of them all.

19:16.620 --> 19:19.920
-What button's that?
-The one where one of us
likes somebody else.

19:21.500 --> 19:23.250
Right...

19:23.250 --> 19:25.920
Can you imagine
what it's gonna be like
when that happens?

19:30.380 --> 19:31.750
Sorry, I gotta go.

19:31.750 --> 19:34.080
♪ ♪

19:36.170 --> 19:38.750
Looks like I won't
have to imagine it.

19:47.830 --> 19:49.620
Andi:
Next, on Andi Mack.

19:49.620 --> 19:52.420
Would you like to go
with me to taste cakes
for your mother's wedding?

19:52.420 --> 19:53.620
Andi:
Who could say no to that?

19:53.620 --> 19:56.380
Saddle up, and get ready
to bride! Woo-hoo!

19:56.380 --> 19:59.250
-You guys find a cake?
-Yeah, I have buttercream
coursing through my veins.

19:59.250 --> 20:01.670
We had your cake,
now you need to eat it, too.

20:01.670 --> 20:03.580
It just would've been nice
for Buffy to at least

20:03.580 --> 20:06.080
give me a heads up that
she's bringing Walker today.

20:06.080 --> 20:07.920
Buffy:
Andi's in a
canoe with Amber...

20:07.920 --> 20:09.620
How did that happen?

20:09.620 --> 20:11.710
Your best friend...
is with him?

20:11.710 --> 20:13.500
-I was never really with him--
-You were!

20:13.500 --> 20:17.580
And now, she is.
That is the #1 violation
of girl code.
